- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper discusses forensic analysis techniques for detecting attacks on the Robot Operating System (ROS), which falls under the domain of cybersecurity. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper specifically focuses on the Robot Operating System (ROS) and its volatile memory forensics, which is a subfield of robotics. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses software tools and techniques for forensic analysis of the Robot Operating System (ROS), which falls under the domain of software engineering. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses techniques for analyzing distributed systems like the Robot Operating System (ROS), which falls under the domain of distributed computing. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses techniques for analyzing and controlling the behavior of robotic systems, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
